Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Input sequences of single-particle indices", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8874562566990304`*^9, 3.887456258704954*^9}, {
  3.8883150838482122`*^9, 
  3.8883150934469776`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"449e637c-f7d0-4628-9d06-\
e4ea8c1dfce7"],

Cell["\<\
Loading of the 168 (86) input sequences of single particle indices, \
corresponding to antidiagonally-dressed Feynman diagrams of disjoint \
Bogoliubov type with a two-body vertex and two non-identical (identical) \
one-body interaction vertices. Contributions with non-identical vertices are \
twice the ones generated by two identical vertices, as the former do not \
possess any vertex permutation symmetry and hence have multiplicity \
corresponding to the one generated by internal single-particle index \
exchanges in the two-body vertex. The fact that 186 \[NotEqual]2 \[Cross]86 \
is a consequence of the presence of diagrams with equivalent one-body \
vertices, which represent the one-body analogue of the \
\[OpenCurlyQuote]Mickey-Mouse-diagrams\[CloseCurlyQuote], generated by three \
two-body vertices. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->CompressedData["
1:eJxTTMoPSmViYGCQAGIQ/fjUjej4H28cu54lJIDokiTzrB4gHaIeBabl+mOP
vGN463gpvhtMi53jV3kPpHW68sG0bn3GJzbOt44/ds4E03WizcyyCm8de+qf
sIDoJKGLjRfV3joqSj8A0+abls0G0b9vhMwF0U+CfhazqL91XPL/L5ielnZJ
